Neural DX Cluster is a next-gen DX monitoring application designed for serious ham radio operators. Unlike traditional clusters that simply display raw text lists, Neural DX uses a "Dual Spectrum" GUI to separate HF traffic (Shortwave) from VHF/UHF/Space traffic.

It analyzes spots in real-time, detects propagation openings (Surges), and ranks stations based on interest using an intelligent scoring algorithm.
